name: Evernote
description: Add an Evernote Instance to connect your existing Evernote account to the Cloud Storage and Documents Hub, allowing you to manage files and folders. You will need your Evernote account information to add an instance.

configuration.name: Evernote Sandbox
configuration.description: Flag indicating whether the Evernote instance is pointed to the Sandbox service

configuration.name: Evernote OAuth Request Token Secret
configuration.description: The OAuth Request Token Secret for Evernote

configuration.name: Evernote OAuth API Key
configuration.description: The OAuth Api Key for Evernote

configuration.name: Evernote OAuth Access Token Expiration Time
configuration.description: Evernote OAuth Access Token Expiration Time

configuration.name: Evernote OAuth User Token
configuration.description: The OAuth User Token for Evernote

configuration.name: Allow Select Fields parameter
configuration.description: Enables use of global fields query parameter to filter response to only specified fields. This will override any existing vendor functionality on the connector

configuration.name: Evernote OAuth API Secret
configuration.description: The OAuth Api Secret for Evernote

configuration.name: Evernote OAuth Callback URL
configuration.description: The OAuth Callback URL for Evernote

configuration.name: Filter null values from the response
configuration.description: Used to enable/disable filtering of null values from the responses.

configuration.name: Default select fields
configuration.description: Generic map used to specify default fields for bulk download and GET /all requests. Each key should be the canonical objectName and values may be specified as a comma-delimited string or a list of strings

resources.description: Deletes a file from your cloud service by its specified path. This endpoint will soft delete your file. Permanent delete is not supported on 3rd party Evernote applications.

parameters.name: path
parameters.description: The full path to the file (e.g. /myDirectory/myFile.txt)

resources.description: Retrieves a single file from your cloud service from a specified path. The file is directly streamed from the cloud storage provider through Cloud Elements, and is not buffered to disk.

parameters.name: path
parameters.description: The full path to the file (e.g. /myDirectory/28158c26-e934-43f4-9062-ec7f0b1ab161) Please note Evernote uses the file ID instead of a filename.

resources.description: Uploads a file to your endpoint cloud service. The file uploaded flows through Cloud Elements. If the destination path includes directories that do not exist, they will be created.

parameters.name: file
parameters.description: The file to be uploaded

parameters.name: path
parameters.description: The full path to the file (e.g. /myDirectory/myFile.txt)

parameters.name: size
parameters.description: The size of the file in bytes (required only for SharePoint)

parameters.name: tags[]
parameters.description: Tags associated with the file

parameters.name: description
parameters.description: Description of the file

parameters.name: overwrite
parameters.description: Overwrite the file if the file exists

resources.description: Copies a file specified by a file path to another file path, leaving the original intact.  If the source file path does not exist an error response is returned.  If the destination path includes directories that do not exist, they will be created.  Copying a file that already exists results in an error response.

parameters.name: path
parameters.description: The full path to the file (e.g. /myDirectory/28158c26-e934-43f4-9062-ec7f0b1ab161) Please note Evernote uses the file ID instead of a filename.

parameters.name: body
parameters.description: A CloudFile object representing the destination file. Path is required and no other fields are supported.

resources.description: Deletes a specific file associated with an ID from your cloud service using its specified path. This  endpoint will soft delete your file. Permanent delete is not supported on 3rd party Evernote applications.

parameters.name: id
parameters.description: The file ID.

resources.description: Retrieves a specific file associated with an ID from your cloud service from a specified path.  The file is directly streamed from the cloud storage provider through Cloud Elements, and is not buffered to disk.

parameters.name: id
parameters.description: The file id. For SharePoint and Dropbox you can double encode the path and pass it as an id

resources.description: Copies a file associated with an ID from a specified file path to another file path, leaving the original intact.  If the source file associated with an ID does not exist an error response is returned.  If the destination path includes directories that do not exist they will be created.  Copying a file that already exists results in an error response.

parameters.name: id
parameters.description: The file id. For SharePoint and Dropbox you can double encode the path and pass it as an id

parameters.name: body
parameters.description: A CloudFile object representing the destination file. Path is required

resources.description: Retrieves specific metadata on a file associated with an ID from your cloud service using its specified path.

parameters.name: id
parameters.description: The file id. For SharePoint and Dropbox you can double encode the path and pass it as an id

resources.description: Update a file's metadata (tags and path) associated with an ID.  For example, if you had a document that was tagged as operations but needed to be tagged as legal, then you would perform a PATCH to update the tag using the tags JSON array field. The PATCH method can update the name or directory of a file as well as move a file by using the path JSON field. You cannot update the size of a file.

parameters.name: id
parameters.description: The file id. For SharePoint and Dropbox you can double encode the path and pass it as an id

parameters.name: body
parameters.description: A CloudFile object with the fields to update. Valid values include path and tags

resources.description: Find the revisions of a file associated with a given ID.

parameters.name: id
parameters.description: The file ID.

parameters.name: pageSize
parameters.description: The page size for pagination, which defaults to 200 if not supplied

parameters.name: page
parameters.description: The start page for pagination, which defaults to 1 if not supplied

resources.description: Retrieves the revision details of a file associated with a revision ID.

parameters.name: id
parameters.description: The file ID.

parameters.name: revisionId
parameters.description: The earliest revision ID.

resources.description: Returns a link that can be used to download the specified file through Cloud Elements.  The link can be used to download the file without providing credentials.

parameters.name: path
parameters.description: The full path to the file (e.g. /myDirectory/28158c26-e934-43f4-9062-ec7f0b1ab161) Please note Evernote uses the file ID instead of a filename.

resources.description: Retrieves the metadata from a single file on your cloud service from a specified path.

parameters.name: path
parameters.description: The full path to the file (e.g. /myDirectory/28158c26-e934-43f4-9062-ec7f0b1ab161) Please note Evernote uses the file ID instead of a filename.

resources.description: Update a file's metadata (tags and path) associated with a path.  For example, if you had a document that was tagged as operations but needed to be tagged as legal, then you would perform a PATCH to update the tag using the tags JSON array field. The PATCH method can update the name or directory of a file as well as move a file by using the path JSON field. You cannot update the size of a file.

parameters.name: path
parameters.description: The full path to the file (e.g. /myDirectory/28158c26-e934-43f4-9062-ec7f0b1ab161) Please note Evernote uses the file ID instead of a filename.

parameters.name: body
parameters.description: A CloudFile object with the fields to update. Valid values include path and tags

resources.description: Retrieves specific resource inside a file associated with an ID from your cloud service

parameters.name: id
parameters.description: The Resource id of the resource inside a specific note

resources.description: Returns all revisons of a file on the cloud service from a specified path.

parameters.name: path
parameters.description: The full path to the file (e.g. /myDirectory/myFile.txt)

parameters.name: pageSize
parameters.description: The page size for pagination, which defaults to 200 if not supplied

parameters.name: page
parameters.description: The start page for pagination, which defaults to 1 if not supplied

resources.description: Retrieves the revision details of a file on the cloud service from a specified path.

parameters.name: path
parameters.description: The full path to the file (e.g. /myDirectory/myFile.txt)

parameters.name: revisionId
parameters.description: The earliest revision ID.

resources.description: Creates a new folder on your cloud service using its specified path.  Creation of the new folder goes through Cloud Elements.  If the destination path includes directories that do not exist they will be created.  Creating a folder that already exists results in an error response.

parameters.name: body
parameters.description: A CloudFile object with the fields to create. Valid values include path

resources.description: Get a list of CloudFiles that are contained in a specified folder on your cloud service specified by a path.

parameters.name: path
parameters.description: The full path to the folder (e.g. /myDirectory)

parameters.name: fetchTags
parameters.description: Whether or not to return the tags for the files in the folder

parameters.name: pageSize
parameters.description: The page size for pagination, which defaults to 200 if not supplied

parameters.name: page
parameters.description: The start page for pagination, which defaults to 1 if not supplied

parameters.name: calculateFolderPath
parameters.description: Whether or not to construct the path for each item in the response. Defaults to true

resources.description: Retrieves a list of CloudFiles that are contained in a specified folder associated with an ID on your cloud service via a specified path.

parameters.name: id
parameters.description: The folder id. For SharePoint and Dropbox you can double encode the path and pass it as an id

parameters.name: fetchTags
parameters.description: Whether or not to return the tags for the files in the folder

parameters.name: pageSize
parameters.description: The page size for pagination, which defaults to 200 if not supplied

parameters.name: page
parameters.description: The start page for pagination, which defaults to 1 if not supplied

parameters.name: calculateFolderPath
parameters.description: Whether or not to construct the path for each item in the response. Defaults to true

resources.description: Retrieves specific metadata on a folder associated with an ID from your cloud service using its specified path.

parameters.name: id
parameters.description: The folder id. For SharePoint and Dropbox you can double encode the path and pass it as an id

resources.description: Update a folder's metadata (path) associated with an ID.  For example, if you had the ID of a folder that was located in the operations directory, but needed to be moved into the legal directory, then you would perform a PATCH using the path JSON field to update the path.  The PATCH method can update the name or directory of a folder also by using the path JSON field. You cannot update the size of a folder.

parameters.name: id
parameters.description: The folder id. For SharePoint and Dropbox you can double encode the path and pass it as an id

parameters.name: body
parameters.description: A CloudFile object with the field to update. Valid values include path

resources.description: Retrieves specific metadata on a folder from your cloud service using its specified path.

parameters.name: path
parameters.description: The full path to the folder (e.g. /myDirectory)

resources.description: Update a folder's metadata (path) associated with its path.  For example, if you had a folder that was located in the operations directory, but needed to be moved into the legal directory, then you would perform a PATCH using the path JSON field to update the path. The PATCH method can update the name or directory path of a folder also by using the path JSON field. You cannot update the size of a folder.

parameters.name: path
parameters.description: The full path to the existing folder (e.g. /myDirectory)

parameters.name: body
parameters.description: A CloudFile object with the field to update. Valid values include path

resources.description: Ping the Element to confirm that the Hub element has a heartbeat.  If the Element does not have a heartbeat, an error message will be returned.

Performs a text search of file names and directory names.  The content of files is not searched.  The search uses substring matching so searching for "exam" will match on "example.txt".  Subdirectories are also searched.  The search returns a list of CloudFiles that match search parameters.

parameters.name: path
parameters.description: The full path to the folder to start searching from (e.g. /myDirectory)

parameters.name: text
parameters.description: Text in the file or folder name

parameters.name: startDate
parameters.description: The start date (based on the created date of the file or folder) if used, end date is required

parameters.name: endDate
parameters.description: The end date (based on the created date of the file or folder) if used, start date is required

parameters.name: tags[]
parameters.description: Any tags associated with the files (not applicable to folders)

parameters.name: pageSize
parameters.description: The page size for pagination, which defaults to 200 if not supplied

parameters.name: page
parameters.description: The start page for pagination, which defaults to 1 if not supplied

resources.description: Retrieves the amount of storage available on your cloud service account.
